\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 the feeling of scarcity is distinct from its physical reality\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Logic and Consequences of Scarcity\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 What happens to our minds when we feel we have too little, and how does that shape our choices and our behaviors?\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 When scarcity captures our attention, it changes how we think\'97whether it is at the level of milliseconds, hours, or days and weeks.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 A tight deadline or a shortage of cash focuses us on the task at hand. With our minds riveted, we are less prone to careless error. This makes perfect sense: scarcity captures us because it is important, worthy of our attention.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 bandwidth \'97 mental capacity\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 fluid intelligence \'97 how we process and make decisions\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Being poor reduces a person\'92s cognitive capacity more than going one full night without sleep. It is not the poor that have less bandwidth as individuals. Rather, it is that the experience of poverty reduces anyone\'92s bandwidth.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Scarcity captures our attention, and this provides a narrow benefit: we do a better job of managing and processing needs; but it costs us as we neglect other concerns and become less effective in the rest of life.\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Focusing and Tunneling\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Scarcity forces all choices. Abstractions become concrete.\'a0\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Scarcity can make us more effective\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 \ul midcourse correction\ulnone \'a0
\f1\b0 \'97 when you\'92re halfway through something and realize that you are running out of time\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 deadlines are benefits if used correctly\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 a deadline leads the current task to be top of mind\
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 when time is short, you get more out of it\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 \ul focus dividend\'a0
\f1\b0 \ulnone \'97 the positive outcome of scarcity capturing the mind\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93An Englishman\'92s mind works best when it is almost too late.\'94 \'97 Max Hastings\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Anecdotally, scarcity of any kind should yield a focus dividend\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Having fewer blueberries, the blueberry poor enjoyed a focus dividend. In a berry throwing game the blueberry rich made more, but the blueberry poor were more careful, therefore more accurate.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 \ul focus dividend
\f1\b0 \ulnone \'a0\'97 heightened productivity when facing a deadline or the accuracy advantage of the blueberry poor\'97comes from our core mechanism: scarcity captures the mind (unavoidably and beyond our control).\'a0\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 imagery of a deadline will be just that, imagined\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 scarcity can capture the mind when we are both thinking fast and thinking slow (Kahneman)\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Instead of saying that scarcity \'91focuses\'92 we could just as easily say that scarcity causes us to\'a0
\f0\b \ul tunnel
\f1\b0 \ulnone : to focus single-mindedly on managing the scarcity at hand\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 focus is positive:
\f1\b0 \'a0focus on what seems important at the time\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 tunneling is not:
\f1\b0 \'a0leads to tunnel and neglect other, possibly more important things\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 \ul goal inhibition
\f1\b0 \ulnone \'a0\'97 focusing on something that matters to you makes you less able to think about other things your care about.\'a0\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 goal inhibition is the\'a0mechanism underlying tunneling\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 if scarcity-induced neglect is insensitive to the weighing of costs and benefits, we ought to see scarcity creating neglect even when it is detrimental to the person\'92s outcomes\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 scarcity captures our minds automatically; and when it does, we do not make trade offs using a careful cost-benefit calculation. We tunnel on managing scarcity both to our benefit and to our detriment.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Immediate scarcity looms large, and important things unrelated to it will be neglected. When we experience scarcity again and again, these omissions can add up.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 scarcity alters how we look at things, makes us choose differently\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Bandwidth Tax\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 bandwidth measures our computational capacity, our ability to pay attention, to make good decisions, to stick with our plans, and to resist temptation\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 scarcity taxes bandwidth\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 noise can hurt concentration, and performance and there are powerful effects of even a slight distraction\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 scarcity generates internal disruptions\'85without realizing it, the brain\'92s resting state \'97 the default network \'97 tends to pull us away from what we are doing, \'a0psychologist call this an \'91intentional blink\'92\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 proactive inference
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 mentioning a word that means more to us makes us focus on that word\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 scarcity affects our mental processor, by constantly loading the mind with other processes, it leaves less \'91mind' for the task at hand\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 scarcity directly reduces bandwidth
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 not someone\'92s inherent capacity, but the capacity they have available for use\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 cognitive capacity
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 psychological mechanisms that underlie our ability to solve problems, retain information, engage in logical reasoning, and so on.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 fluid intelligence\'a0
\f1\b0 \'97 ability to think and reason abstractly and solve problems independent of any specific learning experience\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 executive control
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 underlies our ability to manage our cognitive activities, including planning, attention, initiating and inhibiting actions, and controlling impulses\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Cognitive capacity and executive control are multifaceted and rich in nuance. Scarcity affects both.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Our study revealed that simply raising monetary concerns for the poor erodes cognitive performance even more than being seriously sleep deprived\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 just like the processor that is slowed down by too many applications, the poor here appear worse because some of their bandwidth is being used elsewhere (e.g. thinking about how I\'92m going to pay the bills this month).\'a0\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 many ingredients go into the manufacturing of self-control\'85it depends on how we weigh the future\'85and we appear to do so inconsistently\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93Once you realize that willpower is just a matter of learning how to control your attention and thoughts, you can really begin to increase it.\'94\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 In studies, when we
\f0\b \'a0introduce a small tickle of scarcity, the subjects were suddenly more impulsive
\f1\b0 \'85beyond fluid intelligence, scarcity appears to reduce executive control\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Harvest\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93The same farmer is rich after harvest and poor before harvest\'94\
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 farmers don\'92t save properly and make worse decisions in times of excess and scarcity\
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 \'93The very state of having less money in the months before harvest makes farmers perform less intelligently and show less cognitive control\'94\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Poverty itself taxes the mind\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 The poor have lower effective capacity than those who are well off. This is not because they are less capable, but rather because part of their mind is captured by scarcity
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Lonely\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 The\'a0
\f0\b lonely show impaired bandwidth
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 in this case, less executive control\
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 those who feel lonely in their daily lives have a substantially higher consumption of fatty foods\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Worry\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 worry consistently and predictably taxes bandwidth among rich and poor\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 a taxed bandwidth leads to carelessness\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 So much of what we attribute to talent or personality is predicated on cognitive capacity and executive control.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 All people, if they were poor, would have less effective bandwidth\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Scarcity makes us have fewer mental resources, it doesn\'92t make us make bad decisions, it just leaves us handicapped in decision making\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Packing and Slack\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 We have a \'91time suitcase\'92 that must fit our work, leisure, and family time. We have a money suitcase that must fit our housing, clothing and all our expenses.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 trade-off thinking and opportunity cost on time and money\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 slack
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 space left unused\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 slack comes from abundance, and can sometimes result in inefficiency and waste\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 faced with over-abundance, sometimes people choose not to choose, and it is slack that leaves us free to do so\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 slack not only absolves you of your need to make trade-offs, but it means mistakes do not entail real sacrifice\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs24 planning fallacy
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 we are all too optimistic about future plans, especially when we have lot of slack\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 slack gives room to fail\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 temptation tax \'97 is regressive and levied more heavily on those who have less\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 our biases are not always responsive to the consequences, and they often persist if these consequences become extreme\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 scarcity does not just mean less room to fail, it means a greater opportunity to fail\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 scarcity raises the cost of error and provides more opportunity to err, to make misguided choices\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 In our \'91time and money suitcases\'92 scarcity may create a logistically harder packing problem\'85and the mind, challenged by the psychology that emerges from scarcity, may find itself needing to navigate a world that is computationally more complex.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs24 Slack is not just inefficiency, it is a mental luxury\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
